SWT is throwing this exception because the offsets returned to StyledText by 
its BidiSegmentListener are not properly order or are not within the line 
range.
That is how Styled test the offsets:
if (event.segments[0] != 0) {
	SWT.error(SWT.ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT);
} 	
for (int i = 1; i < segmentCount; i++) {
	if (event.segments[i] <= event.segments[i - 1] || event.segments[i] > 
lineLength) {
		SWT.error(SWT.ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT);
	} 	
}
